g.text: which is the original (not erasure coded) blob data
Celestia block is split into fixed-size data
chunks known as "shares". Shares are the
atomic unit of the Celestia data square.
Original data is first split into shares and
arranged into a k * k matrix. Then the
availableDataRoot of the block Header is
computed as the Merkle root of the binary
Merkle tree with the row and column roots
